Enjoy this poem I wrote for my poetry class! 

The Word Peach

The word peach is 
delectable

Push and pull, desire of 
Necking and 
Secret knowing

Full in the mouth 
and falling
Like fruit

Velvety skin
To puncture into
Tangy nectar, 
slippery flesh 
swirling on my tongue. 

Question 
and reply, lips then tongue and teeth
Satisfaction complete

You’ve heard lots about it but I’m still trying to let it hit me that I’m a graduate. I’ve got an associates degree. I do feel different. I’ve had to break a few ideas that I’ve had about myself that prevented me from going to school in the first place. Like I’m not smart enough. No one talks about how difficult it is to morph into a new you, letting the previous you die. You still mourn even tho you’re growing & improving. Nothing in my adult life has been as pivotal as going to school has been. Photos by @hkemphoto lingerie by @fantasylingerie
